mean_impute <- function(x)
{
  if(is.numeric(x))
  {
    # Find the mode of x
    mean_x <- mean(x)
    # Replace the missing by the mode
    library(tidyr)
    x <- replace_na(x, mean_x) 
  }
return(x)    
}

numeric_impute <- function(d)
{
  for (i in 1:length(d))
  {if (is.numeric(d[[i]])) {
     d[[i]] <- mean_impute(d[[i]])
  }
  }
  return(d)
}

  1. Write the following function. Give examples to test your function.

  • Input: a data frame

  • Output: a data frame with all the missing of variables replaced by the associated means (for numeric variables) or modes (for non-numeric variables).

Hint: Use If-statement to combine the function in Problem 1 and the function in this example

mean_impute <- function(x)
{
  if(is.numeric(x))
  {
    # Find the mode of x
    mean_x <- mean(x)
    # Replace the missing by the mode
    library(tidyr)
    x <- replace_na(x, mean_x) 
  }
return(x)    
}

mode_impute <- function(x)
{
  if(!is.numeric(x))
  {
    # Find the mode of x
    mode_of_x <- names(sort(-table(x)))[1]
    # Replace the missing by the mode
    library(tidyr)
    x <- replace_na(x, mode_of_x) 
  }
return(x)    
}

library(tidyverse)

numeric_impute <- function(d)
{
  for (i in 1:length(d))
  {if (is.numeric(d[[i]])) {
     d[[i]] <- mean_impute(d[[i]])
  }  else{
       d[[i]] <- mode_impute(d[[i]])
  }
  }
  return(d)
}
df <- read_csv('train.csv')
df <- numeric_impute(df)
sum(is.na(df))

graph <- function(d)
{
  for (i in 1:length(d))
  {if (is.numeric(d[[i]])) {
  d[[i]] <- mean_impute(d[[i]])
  }  else{
    print(ggplot()+geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = d[[i]])))
  }
  }
  return(d)
}

  • Output:

    • all possible the density plots of a numeric variable colored by a non-numeric variable

    • all possible the scatter plots.

Hint: Combine this function, this function, and the function in Question 4. One way to combine is creating a new function, quick_plot, and call these three functions within quic_kplot.

library(ggplot2)
graph <- function(d)
{
  for (i in 1:length(d))
  {if (is.numeric(d[[i]])) {
  print(ggplot()+geom_density(mapping = aes(x = d[[i]])))
  }  else{
    print(ggplot()+geom_bar(mapping = aes(x = d[[i]])))
  }
  }
  return(d)
}
df <- read_csv('train.csv')
df <- numeric_impute(df)
df <- graph(df)

SUPERGRAPH <- function(d)
{
  for (i in 1:length(d))
  {if (is.numeric(d[[i]])) {
    for (j in 1:length(d)) {
      if (is.numeric(d[[j]])) {
        print(ggplot()+geom_point(mapping = aes(x = d[[i]],y=d[[j]])))
        
      }
    }
  
  }
    
  }
  return(d)
}
SUPERGRAPH(df)
